This project was migrated from an MLflow-style `MLproject` directory by
`chapkit migrate`. The original files are preserved under `_old/` for
reference. The chapkit wrapper (`main.py`, `Dockerfile`, `compose.yml`,
`pyproject.toml`) sits alongside your train/predict scripts at the root.

## Quick start

### Local (uv)

```bash
uv sync                    # install chapkit + deps into .venv
uv run python main.py       # serve on http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

Open http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs for the OpenAPI UI, or `/health` for a ping.

### Docker

```bash
docker build -t {{ PROJECT_SLUG }} .
docker run --rm -p 8000:8000 {{ PROJECT_SLUG }}
```

The image uses `ghcr.io/dhis2-chap/{{ BASE_IMAGE }}:latest` as its base.
{% if BASE_IMAGE == "chapkit-r-inla" %}
That's an `amd64`-only image (INLA ships x86_64 binaries only); on Apple
Silicon add `--platform=linux/amd64` to both `docker build` and
`docker run`.
{% endif %}

## Running tests

`chapkit test` drives an end-to-end train + predict cycle against the
running service and prints a short report.

```bash
# in one terminal:
uv run python main.py
# in another:
uv run chapkit test
```

## Project layout

- `main.py` â€” chapkit service (generated). Defines the config schema,
  the `ShellModelRunner`, and the `MLServiceBuilder` wiring.
- `Dockerfile`, `compose.yml`, `pyproject.toml`, `postman_collection.json`,
  `README.md`, `.gitignore`, `.dockerignore` â€” generated.
- Your train/predict scripts, helpers, Python packages, lockfiles,
  `LICENSE`, and any arbitrary data/config files (`*.yaml`, `*.json`, ...)
  â€” **unchanged**, at the project root.
- `_old/` â€” the original `MLproject` plus project metadata that chapkit
  regenerated (old `README.md`, `.gitignore`, `pyproject.toml`, etc.),
  example data (`input/`, `output/`, `example_data*/`), and ad-hoc
  runners (`isolated_run.*`). Preserved as-is for reference; nothing in
  here is used by the chapkit service.
{% if HAS_USER_PYPROJECT %}

### Dependencies from your original `pyproject.toml`

Your model's Python dependencies have been auto-merged from
`_old/pyproject.toml` into the generated `pyproject.toml` at the root,
alongside the chapkit entry. The original is preserved under `_old/`
so you can port over anything we did not migrate automatically â€”
optional dep groups, `[tool.*]` config (ruff, mypy, etc.), environment
markers, and custom `[build-system]` backends.
{% endif %}

## Configuration

Edit the `{{ PROJECT_IDENTIFIER }}Config` class in `main.py` to add or adjust
typed fields. At runtime chapkit serialises the validated config to
`config.yml` in the workspace; your scripts read it via whatever YAML
parser they already use (`yaml.load_file` in R, `yaml.safe_load` in Python).

